---
title: KMS Access Control - Who Has Permission?
---
flowchart TD
    subgraph MYTH["❌ Common Misconceptions"]
        M1["Root user has FULL access automatically"]
        M2["Key creator OWNS the key"]
        M3["Root in key policy = blanket grant to everyone"]
    end

    subgraph TRUTH["✅ Reality"]
        T1["NOBODY has automatic access"]
        T2["Creator needs EXPLICIT permission like anyone else"]
        T3["Root in key policy = ENABLES IAM delegation only"]
        T4["Each principal needs explicit kms:* in their identity policy"]
    end

    subgraph AUTH["Three Authorization Mechanisms"]
        A1["Key Policy (required, on key itself)"]
        A2["IAM Policy (on caller, if key policy enables delegation)"]
        A3["KMS Grant (programmatic, per-operation, revocable)"]
    end

    subgraph SPECIAL["Special Rules"]
        S1["kms:CreateKey holder CAN set initial key policy"]
        S2["Cross-account: key policy MUST name external account"]
        S3["AWS managed key: you control NOTHING"]
    end

    MYTH -->|WRONG| TRUTH
    TRUTH --> AUTH
    AUTH --> SPECIAL

    style MYTH fill:#ff4444,color:#fff
    style TRUTH fill:#44bb44,color:#fff
    style AUTH fill:#3366cc,color:#fff
    style SPECIAL fill:#ff9900,color:#fff
